author: @chocopop01
text: It's true, there is no other group out there like BTS.  A lot of artists have a hard time giving generously to up and coming artists because they're worried about being replaced and they want to stay relevant so they withhold information they've acquired in order to maintain their own status.  But BTS is so genuinely kind and thoughtful that they go out of their way to mentor other artists and look for ways to take care of the next generation.  It's really quite remarkable the scope of their generosity in caring for others. ğŸ’œğŸ’œğŸ’œ We see how well they've cared for one another since they became a group.  All from different backgrounds and they gave of themselves to each other. ğŸ’œğŸ’œğŸ’œ Every time I think of Jin being the maknae of his family and being treated as such to suddenly being the eldest of the group and the way he took care of Jungkookie from the very beginning and gave him the love and nurturing as the maknae that he was accustomed to receiving always makes my heart swell.  Jin was so selfless on behalf of the group and it wasn't just JK that he took care of and nurtured, it was the whole maknae line that he did that for.  He put himself in harms way to take care of Jimin when Jimin was being threatened....ğŸ˜¢ğŸ˜­ğŸ’œ And it's clear that they all put the group ahead of themselves to do what is in the best interest of the group as a whole and no one member tries to outshine the others.  They all shine and have so much talent to offer and they all support and lift up one another.  They really are great examples of how to balance pride with humility and how to be of service to others. ğŸ’œğŸ’œğŸ’œ It's no wonder that Army feels so much love for them because even though most of us will never meet them personally and so many have never had the opportunity yet to see them perform live, we still feel that same sort of nurturing from BTS that they give to those they meet personally.  They still very much concern themselves with taking care of Army that they feel about taking care of anyone else in their orbit.  It's really special and I just love these guys so much.

author: @parkgimmy4225
text:
Its the fact that people forget that TXT became trainees even before BTS got so big.

And tbh, at first, TXT were just the "brother group of BTS" for me too. I supported them but i didn't pay much attention to them. I would try to find some similarities between the two groups as well.
But last year, i finally gave TXT a chance and soon i stopped seeing them as just "the brother group of BTS". They now have their own identity in my mind. And although I'm not a Moa, i can still appreciate the amazing discography that they have. 
Comparison with BTS is something that couldn't have been avoided but it's because TXT were so capable themselves that they were able to make a name of their own.

author: @afnanel5485
text:
I'm re-watching this episode. The first time I watched it, I was thrown away by TXT cuteness. But now, I'm more analyzing and processing Suga's words. His words are so wise and eloquent, and his mindset is so enlightening. "You canâ€™t not change. Change is inevitable, what matters is how you change." Those are words of wisdom. He's so true to himself. I aspire to be like that when I reach 30. I'm at that age when he was full of anger and just lost. On IU Palette, he said that he's not like that anymore and that he's calmer these days, and we can clearly see it. He's lighter and balanced, and more talkative.
 If you listen to his songs clearly, you'll see how he's always been criticizing and analyzing the world and how that has paid off eventually, personally, and professionally.

Seeing this made me teary...TXT was there like at the exact moment when I started to feel my life was meaningless and to see them here talking about their story was just a special moment for me. Suga's words and the fact that TXT's hyungs are there to tell them the words which we as fans cannot convey in person is just so comforting to know.  
As a MOA I would like to reiterate the fact that YES TXT came from a privileged point of view with BTS's major support and they will always acknowledge it and live up to people's expectation with double the hard work, especially the expectations of their BTS hyungs who were there to give a push to them towards a brighter future.

text: Taehyun is well spoken while Yeonjun is getting drunk he always smile and he's sooo cute even Suga couldn't help but smile. Min Yoongi is really a great hyung who always look out and appreciate TXT. Both never forget their fans MOA & ARMY. It's true that TXT been through too much pressure because they debuted after BTS success, they need to step up to prove that they got what it takes to be an idols not because they're BTS label mates or younger brothers. They had been through alot.  Being in the same company is an advantage because of BTS success but the pressure is on. Some people might think that the company is already established the reason why it'll be easier for them to move forward but before BTS got really famous just like Suga said TXT also went through the same experienced they had in the past because they were trainees during those times. Luckily, the company grew because of BTS. It true that kpop is already famous during 1st, 2nd & 3rd gen but not as famous when BTS able to achieve billboard & AMA Psy also contribute to kpop & all other idols. BTS paved the way in Western countries & of course globally. Most of the tourists going to SK is because of BTS, Kdrama, Food & others idol group but we can't invalidate the contribution of BTS to SK economic. Now, kpop is famous globally and alot of idols are famous. Soo proud of TXT's achievement they were able to overcome all the pressure.

author: @shyramohsin
text:
i had to take so many breaks from watching because if i didn't, i would have ended up crying and i cannot afford another mental breakdown rn. finally finished watching this 30-minute video after almost 2 hours... ;; i'll have to watch this again some day without breaks to fully appreciate everything, but even as is rn, i feel so happy to have started stanning txt.

i'm j a baby moa who started stanning them when srr promotions were j beginning, so i still have a lot about all members to learn and a lot of txt's history to understand, but yeonjun and taehyun's love for moas, bts, and of course, txt, was so overwhelming. personally, i have, and still do, have a certain kind of boundary between idols and fans that i keep to - it's j a way to make sure there's no dependency and a constant reality check, of course, but the way yeonjun and taehyun were talking about moas made my heart so full. the pure sincerity and appreciation they have for all moas was just... wow.

as two of the members who have the most ambition for the team, it's so wonderful to see them appear together and talk about their hopes and dreams for the team. their dreams for the team will always be supported by the others too, but i genuinely do just hope they all take care of themselves. aiming for the top is natural in most humans, but i just hope they don't forget about their health. i'm sure moas would love to see them succeed without overbearing pain, first and foremost! i understand their passion, but i do hope that they can also constantly see their progress instead of seeing what they're currently lacking.

anyways, i'm really so glad i started stanning txt, and i can't wait for a day when i get to be a part of the sea of moas to see them perform live in front of me.
